Looking at the basemodel above, our strongest predictors in relation to our response variabe, Zsagarin, are Freshman Average, Freshman 5 Star, Sophomore 5 Star, and Senior 5 Star. The Freshman Average has the strongest relationship with a p value close to 0, followed by Sophomore 5 Star with a p value of 0.0410. Freshman 5 Star and Senior 5 Star have the lowest siginficance with p values of 0.0542 and 0.0697 respectively.

  1. The Donner party were a group of pioneers that migrated to California from the Midwest in the mid-1800s. Their story is quite extensive, and tragic in many way (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donner_Party). The data set provided in donner.xlsx gives information on a set of travelers in the party. Specifically, if the traveler was traveling with an immediate family member (MultiFam = 1 if another immediate family member present), the sex of the traveler (Sex = 1 for Female), and Age. The response variable of interest is whether the traveler survived (Survived = 1 for survival).
  1. The data set has 45 observations. Select 30 data points for training the model and 15 points for test data. Clearly show the code that you use to create these sets.

  1. Create a logistic regression model using the training data, and with the three predictors (Multifam, Sex, and Age).
